<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880429-0068 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Washington Mutual Savings Bank </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CFSB SSAVC WAMU WNEWS </CO><TEXT>   Washington Mutual Savings Bank, Seattle, said it is merging its Columbia Federal Savings Bank and Shoreline Federal Savings Bank units, effective today, into a new subsidiary that will operate under the Columbia Federal name.    Washington Mutual said Joseph Evans, 50 years old, formerly senior vice president of Columbia Federal, was named president of the new 26-branch subsidiary, which will have assets of about $700 million. The thrift said J. Cleve Borth, 52, Columbia Federal's former president, was named executive vice president of the parent company and said Leroy T. Hare, 48, formerly president of Shoreline Federal, resigned. </TEXT></DOC>